3)you really don't need to worry about any weapon skills.. after you hit the 20's you won't want to get hit anymore anyway (and if you get close enough to hit something with a weapon.. that thing will hit you back over your pet.. and if you are in a group you are more use medding up mana to get ready for another nuke than piercing a baddie with a little mage dagger.. leave the melee skills up to the tanks (warrior, paladin, shadowknight, monk, etc <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
4)no need to work on Alcohol Tolerance.. but I usually buy a stack of beer and drink one at a time every now and then while I am medding and such.. not enough to make you sway.. but will raise your skill sowlly <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Steelslinger - 53 Dark Elf Mage - Emarr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1642<br> <font color=#333333>(1/20/03 5:04:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Okay...I don't want to start a NEW topic</span><hr size=1> 1 hand blunt (1hb), 2 hand blunt (2hb), and piercing are the 3 weapon skills a caster can have.  So you (A) need a weapon of the proper type, and (B) need to go whack some monsters with them occasionally.  It is much easier to work on weapons skills while you are in a group with fighter types because the mob will focus attention on them and not hit you.  This does not work while solo, because the moment you get into melee range the mob will ignore your pet and attack you.  So don't plan on doing a lot melee damage, but you certainly need to work on some of it a bit.<br>
<br>
One of the biggest reason to jump in and melee occasionally and take some hits is DEFENSE skills (and later you get a DODGE skill).  By increasing these skills, you will benefit much more later in life by taking less damage when you do get hit.<br>
<br>
If you go put some points into 1hb and 2hb right now you will find the trainer happy to oblige you.  But since you already have a higher piercing skill, you cannot train that one further.  The formula you used is *mostly* accurate, but not for casters melee skill which is (Your_level * 3) + 3 . . . instead of the 5's.<br>
<br>
Good job on the sense heading, keep that one maxed out!  It is a definate advantage.<br>
<br>
You can go swimming in the Felwithe pond back there without difficulty, no bad things to bite you.  I learned most of my swimming while bound in Halas and hunting Everfrost and Blackburrow.  There is a big pond in the city entrance that you must cross to exit the zone, so I always swam across.<br>
<br>
Speaking of Blackburrow, I highly recommend it for levels 12-16.  It is really a good place to learn what &quot;dungeons&quot; are like in this game, and controlling pets.<br>
<br>
